        <div id="ccrsmodisalbedo" class="dataset">
          <h3><a href="/ccrsmodisalbedo/">CCRS MODIS albedo over Canada | Albédo MODIS du CCT couvrant le Canada</a></h3>
          <p><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">analysis ready data</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">broadband</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">cog</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">earth observation</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">satellite imagery</span></p>
          <p>Times series of 10-day spectral and broadband albedo products derived at 250-m spatial resolution over Canadian territory and neighboring areas produced at the Canada Centre for Remote Sensing (CCRS) since February 2000 using MODIS L1B C6.1 swath imagery as input. The imagery for all spectral bands was downscaled and re-projected into the Lambert Conformal Conic (LCC) projection at 250-m spatial resolution.  The area size is 5,700 km x 4,800 km (22,800 pixel x 19,200 lines).
Séries temporelles de produits d’albédo spectral et à large bande générés à des intervalles de 10 jours avec une résolut...</p>
          <p><a href="/ccrsmodisalbedo/">Details &rarr;</a></p>
          <h4>Usage examples</h4>
          <ul class="dataatwork-list">
          <li>
            <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.scitotenv.2020.142701" class="" target="_none">Influence of two management practices in the Canadian Prairies on radiative forcing</a> by Liu, J., Worth, D.E., Desjardins, R.L., Haak, D., McConkey, B., Cerkowniak, D.</li></a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://open.canada.ca/data/en/dataset/808b84a1-6356-4103-a8e9-db46d5c20fcf" class="" target="_none">Probability of the annual minimum snow and ice (MSI) presence over Canada</a> by Trishchenko, Alexander P.</li></a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://doi.org/10.1175/BAMS-D-22-0244.1" class="" target="_none">Annual minimum snow/ice extent variations over Greenland since 2000:ice sheet, peripheral areas, and relation to ice mass balance</a> by Trishchenko, A.P., Ungureanu, C.</li></a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://doi.org/10.1139/cjes-2021-0011" class="" target="_none">Landfast ice properties over the Beaufort Sea region in 2000-2019 from MODIS and Canadian Ice Service data</a> by Trishchenko, A.P., Kostylev, V.E., Luo, Y., Ungureanu, C., Whalen, D., Li, J.</li></a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/J.RSE.2019.111297" class="" target="_none">A raster version of the circumpolar Arctic vegetation map (CAVM)</a> by Raynolds, M.K., Walker, D.A., Balser, A., Bay, C., Campbell, M., Cherosov, M.M., Dani�ls, F.J.A., Eidesen, P.B., Ermokhina, K.A., Frost, G.V., Jedrzejek, B., Jorgenson, M.T., Kennedy, B.E., Kholod, S.S., Lavrinenko, I.A., Lavrinenko, O.V., Magn�sson, B., Matveyeva, N.V., Met�salemsson, S., Nilsen, L., Olthof, I., Pospelov, I.N., Pospelova, E.B., Pouliot, D., Razzhivin, V., Schaepman-Strub, G., ?Sib�k, J., Telyatnikov, M.Y., Troeva, E.</li></a>
