        <div id="usgs-landsat" class="dataset">
          <h3><a href="/usgs-landsat/">USGS Landsat</a></h3>
          <p><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">agriculture</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">cog</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">disaster response</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">earth observation</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">geospatial</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">natural resource</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">satellite imagery</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">stac</span></p>
          <p>This joint NASA/USGS program provides the longest continuous space-based record of 
Earth’s land in existence. Every day, Landsat satellites provide essential information 
to help land managers and policy makers make wise decisions about our resources and our environment.
Data is provided for Landsats 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 7, 8, and 9 (excludes Landsat 6).As of June 28, 2023 (<a href="https://www.usgs.gov/landsat-missions/news/changes-coming-landsats-simple-notification-service-amazon-web-service">announcement</a>),
the previous single SNS topic <code>arn:aws:sns:us-west-2:673253540267:public-c2-notify</code> was replaced with
three new SNS topics for different types of scenes.</p>
          <p><a href="/usgs-landsat/">Details &rarr;</a></p>
