        <div id="broad-gnomad" class="dataset">
          <h3><a href="/broad-gnomad/">Genome Aggregation Database (gnomAD)</a></h3>
          <p><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">bioinformatics</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">genetic</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">genomic</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">life sciences</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">population</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">population genetics</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">short read sequencing</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">whole genome sequencing</span></p>
          <p>The Genome Aggregation Database (gnomAD) is a resource developed by an international coalition of investigators that aggregates and harmonizes both exome and genome data from a wide range of large-scale human sequencing projects. The summary data provided here are released for the benefit of the wider scientific community without restriction on use.
The v4.1 data set (GRCh38) spans 730,947 exome sequences and 76,215 whole-genome sequences from unrelated individuals, of <a href="https://gnomad.broadinstitute.org/stats#diversity">diverse ancestries</a>, sequenced sequenced as part of various disease-specific and population genetic studies.
The gnomAD Principal Investigators and team can be found <a href="https://gn</>...</p>
