        <div id="pubseq" class="dataset">
          <h3><a href="/pubseq/">PubSeq - Public Sequence Resource</a></h3>
          <p><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">bam</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">bioinformatics</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">biology</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">coronavirus</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">COVID-19</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">fast5</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">fasta</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">fastq</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">genetic</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">genomic</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">health</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">json</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">life sciences</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">long read sequencing</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">medicine</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">MERS</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">metadata</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">open source software</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">RDF</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">SARS</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">SARS-CoV-2</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">SPARQL</span></p>
          <p>COVID-19 PubSeq is a free and open online bioinformatics public sequence resource with on-the-fly analysis of sequenced SARS-CoV-2 samples that allows for a quick turnaround in identification of new virus strains. PubSeq allows anyone to upload sequence material in the form of FASTA or FASTQ files with accompanying metadata through the web interface or REST API.</p>
