        <div id="roadmapepigenomics" class="dataset">
          <h3><a href="/roadmapepigenomics/">NIH Roadmap Epigenomics</a></h3>
          <p><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">bioinformatics</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">biology</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">epigenomics</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">genetic</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">genomic</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">life sciences</span></p>
          <p>The NIH Roadmap Epigenomics Mapping Consortium was launched with the goal of producing a public resource of human epigenomic data to catalyze basic biology and disease-oriented research. The project has generated high-quality, genome-wide maps of several key histone modifications, chromatin accessibility, DNA methylation and mRNA expression across 100s of human cell types and tissues. To see what data is available, please check the directory listing: <a href="https://roadmapepigenomics.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/index.html">https://roadmapepigenomics.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/index.html</a>.</p>
