        <div id="nasa-usgs-lunar-orbiter-laser-altimeter" class="dataset">
          <h3><a href="/nasa-usgs-lunar-orbiter-laser-altimeter/">NASA / USGS Lunar Orbiter Laser Altimeter Cloud Optimized Point Cloud</a></h3>
          <p><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">elevation</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">lidar</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">planetary</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">stac</span></p>
          <p>The lunar orbiter laser altimeter (LOLA) has collected and released almost 7 billion individual laser altimeter returns from the lunar surface. This dataset includes individual altimetry returns scraped from the Planetary Data System (PDS) LOLA Reduced Data Record (RDR) Query Tool, V2.0. Data are organized in 15˚ x 15˚ (longitude/latitude) sections, compressed and encoded into the Cloud Optimized Point Cloud (COPC) file format, and collected into a Spatio-Temporal Asset Catalog (STAC) collection for query and analysis. The data are in latitude, longitude, and radius (X, Y, Z) format with the p...</p>
          <p><a href="/nasa-usgs-lunar-orbiter-laser-altimeter/">Details &rarr;</a></p>
          <h4>Usage examples</h4>
          <ul class="dataatwork-list">
          <li>
            <a href="https://pdal.io/" class="" target="_none">Point Data Abstraction Library (PDAL)</a> by <a href="https://github.com/PDAL/PDAL" target="_none">PDAL Contributors</a></li></a>
          </li>
