          <p>SondeHub Radiosonde telemetry contains global radiosonde (weather balloon) data captured by SondeHub from our participating radiosonde_auto_rx receiving stations. radiosonde_auto_rx is a open source project aimed at receiving and decoding telemetry from airborne radiosondes using software-defined-radio techniques, enabling study of the telemetry and sometimes recovery of the radiosonde itself.
Currently 313 receiver stations are providing data for an average of 384 radiosondes a day.  The data within this repository contains received telemetry frames, including radiosonde type, gps position, a...</p>
