        <div id="noaa-gfs-bdp-pds" class="dataset">
          <h3><a href="/noaa-gfs-bdp-pds/">NOAA Global Forecast System (GFS)</a></h3>
          <p><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">agriculture</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">climate</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">disaster response</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">environmental</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">meteorological</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">weather</span></p>
          <p>NOTE - Upgrade NCEP Global Forecast System to v16.3.0 - Effective November 29, 2022 See notification <a href="https://www.weather.gov/media/notification/pdf2/scn22-104_gfs.v16.3.0.pdf">HERE</a>
<br/>
<br/>
The Global Forecast System (GFS) is a weather forecast model produced
by the National Centers for Environmental Prediction (NCEP). Dozens of
atmospheric and land-soil variables are available through this dataset,
from temperatures, winds, and precipitation to soil moisture and
atmospheric ozone concentration. The entire globe is covered by the GFS
at a base horizontal resolution of 18 miles (28 kilometers) between grid
points, which is used by the operational forecasters who predict weather
out to 16</>...</p>
