          <h3><a href="/nrel-pds-nsrdb/">NREL National Solar Radiation Database</a></h3>
          <p><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">earth observation</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">energy</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">geospatial</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">meteorological</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">solar</span></p>
          <p>Released to the public as part of the Department of Energy&#39;s Open Energy Data Initiative,
the <a href="https://nsrdb.nrel.gov/">National Solar Radiation Database (NSRDB)</a> is
a serially complete collection of hourly and half-hourly values of the three
most common measurements of solar radiation – global horizontal, direct
normal, and diffuse horizontal irradiance — and meteorological data. These
data have been collected at a sufficient number of locations and temporal and
spatial scales to accurately represent regional solar radiation climates.</p>
