        <div id="allen-hmba-releases" class="dataset">
          <h3><a href="/allen-hmba-releases/">Human and Mammalian Brain Atlas</a></h3>
          <p><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">biology</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">gene expression</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">Homo sapiens</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">life sciences</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">Mus musculus</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">neurobiology</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">non-human primate</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">single-cell transcriptomics</span></p>
          <p>Human and Mammalian Brain Atlas (HMBA) is a major atlas of the BRAIN Initiative Cell Atlas Network (BICAN) that proposes to establish a comprehensive, highly granular cell atlas in complete adult human, macaque, and marmoset brains that links brain structure, function and cellular architecture. Release artifacts have been made available in this OpenData bucket to enable utilization along with their paper publications by the neuroscience community.</p>
