        <div id="census-2020-pl94-nmf" class="dataset">
          <h3><a href="/census-2020-pl94-nmf/">2020 Census Redistricting Data (P.L. 94-171) Noisy Measurement File</a></h3>
          <p><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">census</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">differential privacy</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">disclosure avoidance</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">ethnicity</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">group quarters</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">housing</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">housing units</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">noisy measurements</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">population</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">race</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">redistricting</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">voting age</span></p>
          <p>The 2020 Census Redistricting Data (P.L. 94-171) Noisy Measurement File (NMF) is an intermediate output of the 2020 Census Disclosure Avoidance System (DAS) TopDown Algorithm (TDA) (as described in Abowd, J. et al [2022] <a href="https://doi.org/10.1162/99608f92.529e3cb9">https://doi.org/10.1162/99608f92.529e3cb9</a>, and implemented in the <a href="https://github.com/uscensusbureau/DAS_2020_Redistricting_Production_Code">DAS 2020 Redistricting Production Code</a>). The NMF was generated using <a href="https://github.com/uscensusbureau/DAS_2020_Redistricting_Production_Code/blob/289ee463936a6f0efcf2e378abe410ec01d0e140/source/programs/engine/primitives.py#L183">the Census Bureau&#39;s implementation</a> of the <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2004.00010">Discrete Gaussian Mechanism</a>, calibrated to satisfy <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1605.02065">zero-Concentrated Differential Privacy</a> with <a href="https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/1989323.1989345">bounded neighbors</a>.
<br/>
  <br/>
The NMF values, called <strong>noisy measurements</strong> are the output of applying the Discrete Gaussian Mechanism to </></></></></></>...</p>
