        <div id="wrf-alaska-snap" class="dataset">
          <h3><a href="/wrf-alaska-snap/">Downscaled Climate Data for Alaska (v1.1, August 2023)</a></h3>
          <p><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">agriculture</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">climate</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">coastal</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">earth observation</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">environmental</span><span class="label label-info-sustainability tag link-tag">sustainability</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">weather</span></p>
          <p>This dataset contains historical and projected dynamically downscaled climate data for the State of Alaska and surrounding regions at 20km spatial resolution and hourly temporal resolution. Select variables are also summarized into daily resolutions. This data was produced using the Weather Research and Forecasting (WRF) model (Version 3.5). We downscaled both ERA-Interim historical reanalysis data (1979-2015) and both historical and projected runs from 2 GCM’s from the Coupled Model Inter-comparison Project 5 (CMIP5): GFDL-CM3 and NCAR-CCSM4 (historical run: 1970-2005 and RCP 8.5: 2006-2100)....</p>
