          <p>Genoxus Annotation is a harmonized and curated collection of human genetic variant databases designed to support accurate and salable variant annotation. Variant annotation following genetic testing such as whole genome sequencing (WGS) or whole exome sequencing (WES) is a critical step in identifying and interpreting disease-associated genetic factors. As sequencing technologies continue to generate large volumes of genomic data, robust and well-structured annotation resources are essential for translating raw variant calls into clinically meaningful insights.
