            <a href="https://computationalpathologygroup.github.io/ASAP/" class="" target="_none">ASAP Viewer</a> by <a href="https://www.diagnijmegen.nl/people/geert-litjens/" target="_none">Geert Litjens</a></li></a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://leopard.grand-challenge.org/" class="" target="_none">LEOPARD Challenge</a> by <a href="https://www.diagnijmegen.nl/" target="_none">Diagnostic Image Analysis Group, Radboudumc, Nijmegen</a></li></a>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p><a href="/leopard/#usageexamples">See 2 usage examples &rarr;</a></p>
        </div>
        <div id="gehcai-mapsmr" class="dataset">
          <h3><a href="/gehcai-mapsmr/">Multi-Anatomy Post-Surgical Magnetic Resonance Dataset (MAPSMR)</a></h3>
          <p><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">life sciences</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">machine learning</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">magnetic resonance imaging</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">medical imaging</span></p>
          <p>The MAPSMR dataset is a multi-organ, post-surgical MRI benchmark dataset focused on organ absence and altered anatomy after common abdominal and pelvic surgeries. The dataset includes cases such as cholecystectomy, prostatectomy, nephrectomy, colectomy, hepatectomy, and related procedures, with annotations identifying surgically absent organs and post-treatment anatomical changes.</p>
