        <div id="nasa-operal3dswx-s1v1" class="dataset">
          <h3><a href="/nasa-operal3dswx-s1v1/">OPERA Dynamic Surface Water Extent from Sentinel-1 (Version 1)</a></h3>
          <p><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">cog</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">datacenter</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">earth observation</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">global</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">land</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">orbit</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">radar</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">sentinel-1</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">surface water</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">water</span></p>
          <p>This dataset contains Level-3 Dynamic OPERA Surface Water Extent from Sentinel-1 (DSWx-S1) product version 1.  DSWx-S1 provides near-global geographical mapping of surface water extent over land at a spatial resolution of 30 meters over the Military Grid reference System (MGRS) grid system, with a temporal revisit frequency between 6-12 days. Using Sentinel-1 radar observations, DSWx-S1 maps open inland water bodies greater than 3 hectares and 200 meters in width, irrespective of cloud conditions and daylight illumination that often pose challenges to optical sensors. Forward production of the...</p>
