          <p><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">ocean currents</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">ocean velocity</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">oceans</span></p>
          <p>The Newcastle (NEWC) HF ocean radar system covers an area of the Central Coast, New South Wales, an area subject to the variability of the East Australian Current (EAC) and its coupling with coastal winds, tides, and waves. In this area the EAC separates from the coast and generates several eddies which control the larval species and the higher marine species and ecosystems in which they forage.The NEWC HF ocean radar system consists of two SeaSonde crossed loop direction finding stations located at Sea Rocks (32.441575 S 152.539022 E) and Red Head (33.010245 S 151.727059 E).  These radars ope...</p>
