        <div id="ztf" class="dataset">
          <h3><a href="/ztf/">Zwicky Transient Facility (ZTF)</a></h3>
          <p><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">astronomy</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">object detection</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">parquet</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">survey</span></p>
          <p>The Zwicky Transient Facility (ZTF) is a time-domain astronomy survey that uses the Palomar 48 inch Schmidt telescope and a custom-built wide-field camera to image the night sky in three photometric filters (g, r, and i). It is a fully-automated survey aimed at a systematic exploration of optical transient phenomena. It completes a scan of the observable northern sky approximately every three nights.</p>
