            <a href="https://irsa.ipac.caltech.edu/docs/notebooks/" class="" target="_none">IRSA Notebook Tutorials</a> by <a href="https://irsa.ipac.caltech.edu" target="_none">Caltech/IPAC-IRSA</a></li></a>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p><a href="/ztf/#usageexamples">See 2 usage examples &rarr;</a></p>
        </div>
        <div id="wise-cryo-3band" class="dataset">
          <h3><a href="/wise-cryo-3band/">3-Band Cryo Data | Wide-field Infrared Survey Explorer (WISE)</a></h3>
          <p><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">astronomy</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">imaging</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">satellite imagery</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">survey</span></p>
          <p>The Wide-field Infrared Survey Explorer (WISE) was a NASA Medium Explorer satellite in low-Earth orbit that conducted an all-sky astronomical imaging survey over four infrared bands from 2010-2011. The 3-Band Cryo Data Release contains 3.4, 4.6 and 12 micron (W1, W2, W3) imaging data that were acquired between 6 Aug and 29 Sept 2010 while the detectors were cooled by the inner cryogen tank following the exhaustion of the outer tank.</p>
