        <div id="wise-allsky" class="dataset">
          <h3><a href="/wise-allsky/">All-Sky Data | Wide-field Infrared Survey Explorer (WISE)</a></h3>
          <p><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">astronomy</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">imaging</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">satellite imagery</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">survey</span></p>
          <p>The Wide-field Infrared Survey Explorer (WISE) was a NASA Medium Explorer satellite in low-Earth orbit that conducted an all-sky astronomical imaging survey over four infrared bands from 2010-2011. The All-Sky Release includes all data taken during the WISE full cryogenic mission phase, 7 January 2010 to 6 August 2010, in the 3.4, 4.6, 12, and 22 micron bands (i.e., W1, W2, W3, W4) that were processed with improved calibrations and reduction algorithms.</p>
