        <div id="wise-allwise" class="dataset">
          <h3><a href="/wise-allwise/">AllWISE Data | Wide-field Infrared Survey Explorer (WISE)</a></h3>
          <p><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">astronomy</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">imaging</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">object detection</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">parquet</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">satellite imagery</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">survey</span></p>
          <p>The Wide-field Infrared Survey Explorer (WISE) was a NASA Medium Explorer satellite in low-Earth orbit that conducted an all-sky astronomical imaging survey over four infrared bands from 2010-2011. The AllWISE Data Release combines data from all cryogenic and post-cryogenic survey phases and provides a comprehensive view of the mid-infrared sky. The Images Atlas includes 18,240 FITS image sets at 3.4, 4.6, 12 and 22 microns. The Source Catalog contains position, apparent motion, and flux information for over 747 million objects detected on the Atlas Images.</p>
