        <div id="wise-postcryo" class="dataset">
          <h3><a href="/wise-postcryo/">NEOWISE Post-Cryo Data | Wide-field Infrared Survey Explorer (WISE)</a></h3>
          <p><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">astronomy</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">imaging</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">satellite imagery</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">survey</span></p>
          <p>The Wide-field Infrared Survey Explorer (WISE) was a NASA Medium Explorer satellite in low-Earth orbit that conducted an all-sky astronomical imaging survey over four infrared bands from 2010-2011. The NEOWISE Post-Cryo Data Release contains 3.4 and 4.6 micron (W1 and W2) imaging data that were acquired between 29 September 2010 and 1 February 2011 following the exhaustion of the inner and outer cryogen tanks.</p>
          <p><a href="/wise-postcryo/">Details &rarr;</a></p>
