        <div id="noaa-gsod" class="dataset">
          <h3><a href="/noaa-gsod/">NOAA Global Surface Summary of Day</a></h3>
          <p><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">agriculture</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">climate</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">environmental</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">natural resource</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">regulatory</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">weather</span></p>
          <p>Global Surface Summary of the Day is derived from The Integrated Surface Hourly (ISH) dataset. The ISH dataset includes global data obtained from the USAF Climatology Center, located in the Federal Climate Complex with NCDC. The latest daily summary data are normally available 1-2 days after the date-time of the observations used in the daily summaries. The online data files begin with 1929 and are at the time of this writing at the Version 8 software level. Over 9000 stations&#39; data are typically available. The daily elements included in the dataset (as available from each station) are: <br/>
Mean t...</p>
          <p><a href="/noaa-gsod/">Details &rarr;</a></p>
