        <div id="noaa-nwm-pds" class="dataset">
          <h3><a href="/noaa-nwm-pds/">NOAA National Water Model Short-Range Forecast</a></h3>
          <p><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">agriculture</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">agriculture</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">climate</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">disaster response</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">environmental</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">transportation</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">weather</span></p>
          <p>The National Water Model (NWM) is a water resources model that simulates and forecasts water
budget variables, including snowpack, evapotranspiration, soil moisture and streamflow, over
the entire continental United States (CONUS). The model, launched in August 2016, is designed
to improve the ability of NOAA to meet the needs of its stakeholders (forecasters, emergency
managers, reservoir operators, first responders, recreationists, farmers, barge operators, and
ecosystem and floodplain managers) by providing expanded accuracy, detail, and frequency of water
information. It is operated by NOA...</p>
