        <div id="noaa-wave-ensemble-reforecast" class="dataset">
          <h3><a href="/noaa-wave-ensemble-reforecast/">NOAA Wave Ensemble Reforecast</a></h3>
          <p><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">agriculture</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">climate</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">meteorological</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">weather</span></p>
          <p>This is a 20-year global wave reforecast generated by WAVEWATCH III model (<a href="https://github.com/NOAA-EMC/WW3">https://github.com/NOAA-EMC/WW3</a>) forced by GEFSv12 winds (<a href="https://noaa-gefs-retrospective.s3.amazonaws.com/index.html">https://noaa-gefs-retrospective.s3.amazonaws.com/index.html</a>). The wave ensemble was run with one cycle per day (at 03Z), spatial resolution of 0.25°X0.25° and temporal resolution of 3 hours. There are five ensemble members (control plus four perturbed members) and, once a week (Wednesdays), the ensemble is expanded to eleven members. The forecast range is 16 days and, once a week (Wednesdays), it extends to 35 days. More information about the wave modeling, wave grids and calibration can be found in the WAVEWATCH III regtest ww3_ufs1.3 (<a href="https</></>...</p>
          <p><a href="/noaa-wave-ensemble-reforecast/">Details &rarr;</a></p>
          <h4>Usage examples</h4>
