          <p>The mission of the Ocean Climate Stations (OCS) Project is to make meteorological and 
oceanic measurements from autonomous platforms.  Calibrated, quality-controlled, and well-documented 
climatological measurements are available on the OCS webpage and the OceanSITES Global Data
Assembly Centers (GDACs), with near-realtime data available prior to release of the complete, 
downloaded datasets.<br/><br/>OCS measurements served through the Big Data Program come from OCS high-latitude moored buoys located in the Kuroshio 
Extension (32°N 145°E) and the Gulf of Alaska (50°N 145°W).  Initiated in 2004 and 20...</p>
