          <p>Our collection encompasses approximately one million vascular plant specimens from the Mediterranean and Middle East biodiversity hotspot, representing flora from Israel, Jordan, Hermon, Sinai, Egypt, the Caucasus, Arabia, North Africa, and throughout the Mediterranean basin. This scientifically significant repository includes published voucher specimens, original specimens used for &quot;Flora Palaestina&quot; illustrations, and critical references for the Israeli gene bank collections. The ongoing digitization process captures high-resolution images of each specimen while systematically inco...</p>
