          <h3><a href="/aodn_animal_ctd_satellite_relay_tagging_delayed_qc/">Marine Animal - Satellite Relay Tagging -  Quality controlled profiles</a></h3>
          <p><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">biology</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">chemical biology</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">chemistry</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">marine mammals</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">oceans</span></p>
          <p>CTD (Conductivity-Temperature_Depth)-Satellite Relay Data Loggers (CTD-SRDLs) are used to explore how marine animal behaviour relates to their oceanic environment. Loggers developed at the University of St Andrews Sea Mammal Research Unit transmit data in near real-time via the Argo satellite system. Data represented here was collected in the Southern Ocean, from elephant, fur and Weddell Seals. In 2024 data was added from flatback and olive ridley turtles, from a pilot study co-funded by the Royal Australian Navy in collaboration with the Australian Institute of Marine Science and Indigenous ...</p>
