        <div id="aodn_vessel_xbt_delayed_qc" class="dataset">
          <h3><a href="/aodn_vessel_xbt_delayed_qc/">Ships of Opportunity - Expendable bathythermographs - Delayed mode</a></h3>
          <p><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">oceans</span></p>
          <p>IMOS Ship of Opportunity Underway Expendable Bathythermographs (XBT) group is a research and data collection project working within the IMOS Ship of Opportunity Multi-Disciplinary Underway Network sub-facility. Five major (HRX) high-resolution XBT lines provide boundary to boundary profiling and closely spaced sampling to resolve mesoscale eddies, fronts and boundary currents. The lines are repeated 4 times per year by an on-board technician. The routes sample each major boundary current system using available commercial vessel traffic. All of the transects transmit data in real-time. The data...</p>
          <p><a href="/aodn_vessel_xbt_delayed_qc/">Details &rarr;</a></p>
