        <div id="pyenvs-and-callargs" class="dataset">
          <h3><a href="/pyenvs-and-callargs/">PyEnvs and CallArgs</a></h3>
          <p><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">code completion</span><span class="label label-info tag link-tag">machine learning</span></p>
          <p>PyEnvs is a collection of 2814 permissively licensed Python packages along with their isolated development environments. Paired with a program analyzer (e.g. Jedi Language Server), it supports querying for project-related information. CallArgs is a dataset built on top of PyEnvs for function call argument completion. It provides function definition, implementation, and usage information for each function call instance.</p>
